            <div type="translation" source="bib:Hultzsch1896-1897_05">
                
                <p n="1">
                    Prosperity! In the thirty-second year <supplied reason="subaudible">of the reign</supplied> of king Parakēsarivarman who conquered Madirai. <supplied reason="subaudible">This is</supplied> the spot on the embankment, at which a tiger was stabbed by Kumāra-<unclear>Na</unclear>ndai Puḻa<unclear>la</unclear>ppaṉ of Mukkuṭṭūr, a village on the northern bank <supplied reason="subaudible">of the Pālāṟu river</supplied>.
                </p>   
                
            </div>
            
            <div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
                
                <p n="1">
                    Prosperity!
                </p>
                
                <p n="2-6">
                    Thirty-second year of the king Parakesarivarman who took Maturai.
                </p>
                
                <p n="4-12">
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">This is</supplied> the enbankment <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>karai</foreign></supplied> place <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nāṭu</foreign></supplied> where
                    Kumāra Nantai Puḻalappaṉ <supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> Mukkuṭṭūr, <supplied reason="explanation">on</supplied> the northern bank,
                    pierced/stabbed <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kuttiṉa</foreign></supplied> a tiger.
                </p>
            </div>
            
